text: First up is going to be Alexandre Pacheco da Silva from Brazil on the free flow of information

"Increasingly, governments are pushing for stronger rules around data localization - forcing platforms and app makers to host data about users and customers within a specific locale. This has big implications for how costly it is to start up a new business online, and in how services are designed going forwards. This session will give an update on these upcoming laws, and where developers can make a difference."
